  <h1>Electrolux Professional Commercial Dishwasher Repair — Los Angeles &amp; SoCal</h1>

  <p>First, the clarification that every Electrolux Professional operator eventually has to make when calling for service: Electrolux Professional is not the same company as residential Electrolux. Electrolux Professional AB is a separate Swedish company — it listed independently on Nasdaq Stockholm in 2020 — that manufactures commercial foodservice equipment under three brands: Electrolux Professional, Zanussi Professional, and AEG Professional. When you call a residential Electrolux repair company with a commercial Electrolux Professional dishwasher, you'll usually get a polite decline or, worse, a technician who shows up without the right diagnostic knowledge for the equipment.</p>

  <p>In the LA market, Electrolux Professional dishwashers show up in upscale hotels, European-leaning restaurant groups, and institutional food service operations that specified them for energy and water efficiency. The Green &amp; Clean series — Electrolux Professional's current commercial dishwasher line — uses significantly less water per rack than older commercial dishwashers, which matters to LA operators watching their water bills and sustainability numbers. We service the full Electrolux Professional commercial dishwasher range throughout LA County, Orange County, Ventura, and the Inland Empire. $120 commercial diagnostic applied to the repair. Call <strong>{phone}</strong>.</p>

  <h2>Electrolux Professional Equipment We Service</h2>

  <h3>EHT / EHW Series — Undercounter Dishwashers &amp; Glasswashers</h3>
  <p>The EHT series undercounters and EHW glasswashers are Electrolux Professional's compact machines — bars, café service stations, and smaller restaurant back-of-house operations. These are distinctly different from residential Electrolux dishwashers in every way: the wash circuit, the booster heater architecture, the control board, and the available error codes. The EHT undercounters use Electrolux Professional's AirBreak system to prevent back-siphoning — a drain break valve that's a common confusion point for technicians who work on residential Electrolux and encounter it unexpectedly on a commercial unit. The AirBreak valve can scale in LA hard water and restrict drain flow; it presents as a drainage problem but clears quickly once descaled.</p>
  <p>The door switch on EHT undercounters is another common LA service call — the interlock is more sensitive than on equivalent Hobart or Jackson units, and in a high-cycle bar environment the switch contact wears faster. Machine won't start, no error code. Half the time it's the door switch, same as on Champion UH undercounters.</p>
  <p><strong>Models:</strong> EHT8IG, EHT8IGLE, EHW8IG (glasswasher), Green &amp; Clean undercounter series</p>

  <h3>Passthrough &amp; Hood-Type Dishwashers</h3>
  <p>Electrolux Professional's passthrough (hood-type) machines serve mid-volume restaurant and hotel dining room operations. The current Green &amp; Clean passthrough series uses bi-directional wash arms — wash arms that rotate in both directions during a cycle — which improves coverage compared to single-direction designs, particularly on the undersides of items in the upper rack. When the wash arms develop scale deposits on the nozzle openings (LA hard water, again), the bi-directional system doesn't fully compensate for reduced spray pressure — you need to clean both the nozzles and the bearing that allows the arm to reverse direction. Most general technicians clean the nozzles and miss the bearing.</p>
  <p>The SMART drain pump on current Electrolux Professional hood machines is a variable-speed drain pump that adjusts flow rate based on tank level. When the pump's speed control module fails, the tank doesn't drain fully between cycles — wash water contaminates with food debris, temperatures drop, wash quality degrades over successive cycles rather than failing immediately. The diagnosis requires understanding that the drain pump has a speed controller, not just testing whether the pump motor runs.</p>
  <p><strong>Models:</strong> Green &amp; Clean passthrough series, ECS series, SIF series, Line 5000 hood-type</p>

  <h3>Conveyor &amp; Flight-Type</h3>
  <p>Electrolux Professional's conveyor and flight-type machines are found in LA's larger hotel banquet operations and university dining systems that specified them for their water efficiency metrics — the Green &amp; Clean conveyor line uses substantially less water per rack than equivalent Hobart or Jackson conveyors. The Aqualine water connection system on current Electrolux Professional conveyors uses a heat exchanger to pre-heat incoming cold water using exhaust heat — similar in concept to Meiko's ComfortAir, but specific to the Electrolux Professional plumbing architecture. When the Aqualine heat exchanger scales in LA water, incoming water temperature entering the machine is lower than spec, requiring the wash heaters to compensate — energy consumption rises before wash temperature errors appear.</p>
  <p><strong>Models:</strong> Green &amp; Clean conveyor series, flight-type Electrolux Professional, SIF 61 series</p>

  <h2>The Zanussi Professional &amp; AEG Professional Connection</h2>

  <p>Electrolux Professional AB sells the same commercial dishwasher platforms under three brand names depending on the market and distribution channel: Electrolux Professional, Zanussi Professional, and AEG Professional. If you have a Zanussi Professional or AEG Professional commercial dishwasher, you have the same machine — same engineering, same parts, same service requirements — as an equivalent Electrolux Professional model. We service all three brand designations under the Electrolux Professional AB umbrella.</p>

  <p>This matters practically: operators who search for "Zanussi Professional dishwasher repair LA" or "AEG Professional dishwasher service" sometimes find residential repair companies that know the consumer Zanussi or AEG brand but not the commercial platform. Commercial Zanussi Professional equipment is not the same as the residential Zanussi dishwashers sold in European markets. The service requirements, parts, and diagnostic protocols are those of a professional commercial warewasher.</p>

  <h2>LA Hard Water and Electrolux Professional Equipment</h2>

  <p>The Green &amp; Clean series' water efficiency design — using less water per rack — has an unintended consequence in LA's hard water environment. Less water per cycle means higher mineral concentration in the wash tank as cycles accumulate without a full tank refresh. Scale accumulates on the heating element, spray arm nozzles, and the AirBreak valve faster than on higher-water-consumption machines running the same number of racks. Electrolux Professional's own technical guidance for high-hardness water areas recommends more frequent deliming than their standard maintenance schedule — we apply that guidance to every machine we service in the LA market.</p>

  <p>Quarterly descaling of the heating element and spray arm system. Monthly inspection of the AirBreak drain valve for scale restriction. For the Aqualine heat exchanger on conveyor models, semi-annual descaling at minimum. These are the intervals appropriate for SoCal's water, not the standard annual schedule that works in softer-water markets.</p>

  <h2>Recent Electrolux Professional Service Calls</h2>

  <h3>"EHT undercounter — not draining, bar West Hollywood"</h3>
  <p>Electrolux Professional EHT undercounter at a cocktail bar — machine completing cycles but leaving water in the tank at the end of drain. Previous technician had diagnosed a drain pump failure and ordered a pump. We arrived before the part was installed to do our own assessment. Found the AirBreak valve partially blocked by scale — the valve's small-bore drain passage had scaled down to about 30% of its original diameter. The SMART drain pump was working correctly but couldn't push water through the restricted valve fast enough to complete the drain cycle within the programmed time. Descaled the AirBreak valve, verified full drain within spec. Pump was fine. Saved the operator a pump replacement that wasn't needed.</p>

  <h3>"Green &amp; Clean passthrough — wash quality degrading, hotel Silver Lake"</h3>
  <p>Boutique hotel's Electrolux Professional passthrough, gradual wash quality decline over two months. Dishes coming out with residue on undersides — consistent pattern suggesting the upper spray arms specifically. Found two issues: the bi-directional wash arm bearing had scale buildup preventing the arm from reversing correctly, so it was effectively running single-direction only. And the SMART drain pump's speed controller was producing intermittent drain issues — tank wasn't fully refreshing between cycles, so carryover food particles were contaminating wash water. Cleaned the bearing, descended the spray arm nozzles, replaced the drain pump speed controller module. Wash quality restored. Set the hotel on quarterly spray arm maintenance and monthly drain cycle verification.</p>

  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <p><strong>Is Electrolux Professional the same as residential Electrolux?</strong><br>
  No. Electrolux Professional AB is a separate company from AB Electrolux (the consumer appliance maker). They use the same "Electrolux" name but operate independently — Electrolux Professional listed separately on Nasdaq Stockholm in 2020. Their commercial dishwashers are engineered differently, use different parts, and require different diagnostic knowledge than residential Electrolux appliances. We service Electrolux Professional commercial equipment specifically — not residential Electrolux.</p>

  <p><strong>Do you service Zanussi Professional and AEG Professional dishwashers?</strong><br>
  Yes. Electrolux Professional AB sells the same commercial platforms under Zanussi Professional and AEG Professional brand names in different markets. Same engineering, same parts, same service. We service all three brand designations.</p>

  <p><strong>My Electrolux Professional undercounter isn't draining — is it the pump?</strong><br>
  Not necessarily. On EHT undercounters, incomplete drainage is often caused by the AirBreak valve scaling in LA hard water — the valve passage restricts and the pump can't clear the tank within the cycle's drain time. We check the AirBreak valve before assuming pump failure. A scaled valve is a $0 fix compared to a pump replacement. Call {phone} for a same-day diagnosis.</p>

  <p><strong>What is the Green &amp; Clean series?</strong><br>
  Green &amp; Clean is Electrolux Professional's current commercial dishwasher line, designed for lower water and energy consumption per rack. In LA, the water efficiency is a selling point for operators monitoring utility costs and sustainability metrics. The tradeoff in our market is that lower water volume per cycle concentrates mineral scale faster — maintenance intervals need to be shorter than Electrolux Professional's standard recommendations for average water hardness.</p>

  <p><strong>What is your diagnostic fee?</strong><br>
  $120 commercial diagnostic, applied to the repair when you proceed. On-site quote — what we quote is what's on the invoice.</p>

